      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Software used in the FEA ensemble (Ansys Mechanical 2022 R1) must be qualified under an established SQA plan with documented version control, issue tracking, and validation test suite.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2022 R1 is used under a documented SQA plan maintained by DePuy Synthes and FDA OSEL. Version control via Git, issue tracking in JIRA, and a regression test suite covering linear static and contact mechanics benchmarks are in place. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA code verified against ASME V&V 10.1 benchmark problems relevant to structural contact mechanics.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical has been verified against ASME V&V 10.1 benchmark set including beam bending, contact patch tests, and nonlinear material benchmarks. Results agree within 0.5% of analytical solutions. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study must demonstrate QoI change less than 2% between successive refinements; Richardson extrapolation applied to estimate discretization error.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh convergence study was performed on the pedicle screw-rod-vertebra block assembly. QoI (stiffness, yield force) changed by less than 1.1% between the medium and fine meshes. Richardson extrapolation gives a discretization error estimate of 0.8% for stiffness and 1.4% for yield force. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver convergence tolerances documented; force and displacement residuals below 1e-4 at each load step.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear Newton-Raphson solver used with force residual tolerance 1e-5 and displacement residual tolerance 1e-5. Convergence achieved at all 50 load steps for all 11 model instances. No divergence events recorded. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented simulation protocol with independent peer review of model setup; checklist-based review completed by a second analyst.",
      "rationale": "A written simulation protocol was followed for all model instances. An independent FDA OSEL analyst reviewed boundary conditions, material assignments, contact definitions, and load application against the protocol checklist. No discrepancies identified. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form (continuum linear elastic with frictional contact) justified by literature and material characterization; alternative model forms considered and documented.",
      "rationale": "Continuum linear elastic constitutive model with frictional Coulomb contact (mu=0.2, titanium-titanium) selected based on prior published validation studies for spinal implant constructs under quasi-static loading. Geometric nonlinearity included to capture large-displacement effects at 40 mm. Alternative viscoelastic and elastoplastic forms considered; elastoplastic form adopted for post-yield prediction. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric parameters sourced from coupon testing and CMM measurements; input uncertainty quantified using measurement uncertainty propagation.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V ELI material properties (E=114 GPa, yield 880 MPa, UTS 950 MPa) obtained from tensile coupon testing per ASTM E8. Geometric dimensions obtained from CMM measurement of each of the 11 constructs with reported measurement uncertainty. Input parameter uncertainty was propagated through the model ensemble using a Monte Carlo approach with 200 samples, yielding combined model uncertainty uval used in the E/uval metric. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 test samples with documented traceability; samples representative of production geometry and material lot.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories. All constructs sourced from the same production lot with documented material certificates. CMM inspection confirmed dimensional conformance to drawing. Sample size exceeds minimum N=10 threshold. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must span at least two load levels or two environmental conditions representative of the COU; inter-laboratory reproducibility documented.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single load condition (ASTM F1717 static compression-bending at a single offset distance). Inter-laboratory reproducibility demonstrated with coefficient of variation below 5% across the two laboratories. However, only one test condition (load configuration) was evaluated, which does not meet the Gradation 3 requirement for condition breadth. Gradation 2 achieved; this factor is below the required level but accepted given the standardized nature of ASTM F1717 and the direct regulatory precedent."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model inputs matched to experimental measurements for each of the 11 constructs; documented mapping between physical measurements and model parameters.",
      "rationale": "Each of the 11 FEA model instances was parameterized using CMM measurements from the corresponding physical construct. Material properties were taken from the same production lot coupon data. Boundary conditions replicate the F1717 fixture geometry. A formal input equivalency table documents the mapping for each construct. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 for all primary QoIs; percentage difference < 10% for all QoIs.",
      "rationale": "All three primary QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) meet the acceptance criteria: maximum E/uval = 1.88 (force at 40 mm), maximum percentage difference = 7.5% (force at 40 mm). Both thresholds satisfied for all QoIs across all 11 constructs. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs must be directly linked to the clinical failure mode and the regulatory submission claim; documented traceability from QoI to hazard.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and are directly linked to the clinical failure mode of pedicle screw fatigue fracture under cyclic loading. A hazard traceability matrix links each QoI to the corresponding failure mode and regulatory claim. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario must match the COU geometry, loading, and boundary conditions; any extrapolation from validation to COU documented and bounded.",
      "rationale": "The validation activity uses the identical non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw geometry, the same ASTM F1717 fixture, and the same quasi-static loading protocol as the COU. No extrapolation in geometry or loading is required. The validation scenario is considered directly relevant to the COU with no significant gap. Gradation 3 achieved."
    }
  ],
