    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/org/fda-cdrh-osel",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU1 is accepted. All 13 V&V 40 factors have been assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed the required credibility level. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is accepted based on the standardized and well-precedented nature of the ASTM F1717 single-condition test protocol and the availability of inter-laboratory reproducibility data. All primary QoIs satisfy the pre-established acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96 and percentage difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is accepted as sufficiently credible to support the regulatory submission claim for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design.",
